<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-03-19</DATELINE><TITLE>Do children need a longer time to shed SARS-CoV-2 in stool than adults?</TITLE><BODY>Abstract SARS-CoV-2 can be shed in the stool of patients in the recovery phase. Children show a longer shedding time than adults. We analyzed the possible causes of this finding and recommend that a negative stool sample be included in a patient's discharge criteria.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>